name: coke production | steam, in chemical industry | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/30365/documentation

The multioutput-process represents the supply of coke, producing coal gas, coal tar, sulfur and benzene as a byproduct.;This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.;This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.  Weights are based on production volumes.;CN, wet quenching: weight = 73.92 %;CN, dry quenching: weight = 22.08 %;US: weight = 2.277 %;DE: weight = 1.717 %;For more details please see the regional datasets

Activity starts with the reception of coal at plant-site.

The activity ends with the supply of 1 kg of coke, considering the by-product recovery, to global market. Transport is not included.
category: C:Manufacturing/19:Manufacture of coke and refined petroleum products/191:Manufacture of coke oven products/1910:Manufacture of coke oven products

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: CN (dry and wet quenching), US, DE.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.  Weights are based on production volumes.;CN, wet quenching: weight = 73.92 %;CN, dry quenching: weight = 22.08 %;US: weight = 2.277 %;DE: weight = 1.717 %
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription:
This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.  Weights are based on production volumes.
CN-AH: production volume = 1.06e+13 MJ/year, weight = 0.7392
CN: production volume = 3.16e+12 MJ/year, weight = 0.2208
US: production volume = 3.25e+11 MJ/year, weight = 0.02277
DE: production volume = 2.45e+11 MJ/year, weight = 0.01717
